metadata.name: The Far East. Japanese islands
metadata.description:
Georgiy Chernyavsky 
National Artist of the USSR, Laureate of the Taras Shevchenko Prize of the USSR. Georgiy Chernyavsky died in Kyiv. Buried in Baikove Cemetery. His artworks are famous in Central Asia, Hungary, Poland, Finland and Cyprus. Author of “Odessa Port” and “Far East Japanese Islands”.

"The Far East. Japanese islands ". Paper, watercolor 1974 Work from the series of the artist's journey to the Far East. It was exhibited at an exhibition of Soviet artists in Japan in 1975. In Moscow it was exhibited in the Manege under the name "Soviet Kurils".
